==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jovinianist
<hw>Jo*vin"ian*ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Script.
Hist.)</fld> <def>An adherent to the doctrines of
<persfn>Jovinian</persfn>, a monk of the fourth century, who denied the
virginity of <persfn>Mary</persfn>, and opposed the asceticism of his
time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jowl</ent>⟦br⟧
